crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The analyzed sample is a sophisticated backdoor or spyware designed for data exfiltration and persistent surveillance. It employs several advanced techniques common in malware: 1. Stealth and Anti-Analysis: It uses a manual import resolution routine (sub_40182a) and dynamic API loading via GetProcAddress/LoadLibraryA to hide its true capabilities from static IAT analysis. It also performs process masquerading by modifying the ImagePathName and CommandLine within the Process Environment Block (PEB) in sub_40380c. 2. Data Collection: The binary contains a dedicated screen capture routine (sub_404255) that generates BMP files and manages them via the registry. It also collects system metadata, volume information, and enumerates processes. 3. Command and Control (C2): Function sub_4031ee implements network communication using HTTP POST requests with custom-formatted data (%.8x=%s&%.8x=%s). 4. Cryptography and Obfuscation: It utilizes custom stream ciphers for string decryption (sub_4016d5, sub_4017aa) and a rolling hashing/cryptographic algorithm (sub_401c16). Relevant IOCs include the Base64 alphabet string used in sub_4012a4, registry manipulation for exfiltration tracking, and the use of the .BMP file extension for captured data.
